lead_paragraph: OAKLAND, Calif., Sept. 21 (AP) — Rich Harden struck out seven in an impressive return from the disabled list, and Jason Kendall hit a pair of two-run singles in the Oakland Athletics’ 7-4 victory over the Cleveland Indians.
